<HEADLINE>
HIGH WIRE ACT JOINS SANTA ANITA DERBY FIELD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA, Calif. _ High Wire Act has joined the field for
Saturday's Santa Anita Derby, and although he isn't the horse to
beat, he is the one to catch.
</P>
<P>
   The John Shirreffs-trained gelding zoomed to a seven-length lead
and finished third behind Prime Timber and Exploit when he was
ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye in the March 13 San Felipe Stakes. The
son of End Sweep will be the only confirmed front-runner in the
1[-mile Derby.
</P>
<P>
   Who'll ride him Saturday was undetermined Tuesday, with Chris
McCarron a possibility if he doesn't end up with General Challenge.
</P>
<P>
   High Wire Act, owned by 505 Farms, has won two of three starts.
He encouraged Shirreffs by working 7 furlongs in 1:252/5 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Bob Baffert withdrew Finder's Gold, who worked 6
furlongs in a slow 1:13 on Monday. The trainer still has favorite
Prime Timber and General Challenge.
</P>
<P>
   Others expected to be entered Thursday morning: Desert Hero,
Honest Lady and Capsized.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
