   PRODUCTIVITY-STUDY (Washington) _ After years of maintaining
that its statistics on the labor productivity growth rate were
generally reliable, the government agency that produces the numbers
now says they may be somewhat underestimated. In research to be
published on Wednesday, the Labor Department's Bureau of Labor
Statistics says that the current economic prosperity, and rising
profits ``do not seem fully consistent with slow productivity
growth.'' By Louis Uchitelle.
