<HEADLINE>
MLS COMMISSIONER TO ENTER CIENFUEGOS NEGOTIATIONS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ Major League Soccer Commissioner Doug Logan
said Tuesday he will meet with Galaxy midfielder Mauricio
Cienfuegos and his agent, Corey Clemetson, on Thursday in an effort
to settle Cienfuegos' contract dispute.
</P>
<P>
   Cienfuegos and fellow Salvadoran Raul Diaz Arce of San Jose have
been at odds with the league over their contracts since training
camp opened in February.
</P>
<P>
   Both Cienfuegos and Diaz Arce ended camp-long holdouts March 20
to attend their clubs' season openers. However, both vowed to sit
out Saturday's Galaxy-Clash game and likely head home to El
Salvador if an agreement isn't reached this week.
</P>
<P>
   Clemetson, who represents both players, says little progress has
been made in the past week, despite Logan's claims that a
substantial offer is on the table.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have made both players aggressive offers to extend their
contracts out a number of years,'' Logan said during a conference
call. ``We are hopeful we can reach an agreement before the week is
done.''
</P>
<P>
   Logan said renegotiating contracts isn't something he's inclined
to do, but he is willing to make an exception this time.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is no incentive on our part to go out there and rip up
the contracts,'' Logan said. ``Otherwise, the integrity of the
relationships with players in this league would be in jeopardy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Still, we want them to stay with us a long time. But at the
end of the day, they have to make up their minds, and they have to
make their choices.''
</P>
<P>
   Clemetson wouldn't comment on the offers, but laughed at Logan's
comment that they were ``aggressive.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Let's just say we haven't made much progress in the last
week,'' Clemetson said.
</P>
<P>
   Clemetson acknowledged that Diaz Arce has left San Jose to be in
Los Angeles with Cienfuegos until Thursday's meeting. Cienfuegos,
however, is still practicing with the Galaxy.
</P>
<P>
   ``We will try to find a way to get the deal done,'' Clemetson
said. ``Both players are hoping they can be in uniform this
weekend, but we don't know if that will happen.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are going to make every effort possible for Mauricio and
Raul to work something out. But it's their decision, and it has to
be something they are both happy with.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-31-99 0214EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
