<P>
   The New York Times is planning a five-page package of stories
and graphics on the continuing crisis in Kosovo:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MILITARY (Brussels) _ NATO's senior military officer says
the goal of expanded air strikes is to loosen Milosevic's grip on
power. By Michael Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RUSSIA (Moscow) _ Russia says it's sending part of its
Black Sea Fleet through the Bosporus to monitor Kosovo crisis. By
Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-ASSESS (Dateline to kum) _ A news analysis on a new-style
conflict, ``the endless war.'' By R.W. Apple Jr.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-REBELS (Washington) _ What has happened to the Albanian
leadership. By Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-ALBANIA (Dateline to kum) _ Developments: Serbs fire
shells across the border into Albania; more accounts from stunned
refugees. By John Kifner.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels) _ A senior NATO general tells of the
meetings and decisions leading up to the attack on Serb forces. By
Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-SOLANA (Brussels) _ A man-in-the-news profile of the head
of NATO: Javier Solana Madariaga, who as secretary general of NATO
is running the biggest air war the alliance has ever fought in 50
years of existence, opposed Spain's entry into the organization as
a young Socialist opposition politician in the early 1980s. By
Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-HACKERS (Undated) _ Hackers from Belgrade clog up the
NATO website.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-BELGRADE (Belgrade) _ Yugoslav officials show reported
bomb damage. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-WARCRIMES (Paris) _ The international war crimes tribunal
says it has indicted the Serb paramilitary leader Zeljko
Raznjatovic, known as Arkan, Arkan on charges of war crimes in
Bosnia. It also says that it has warned Milosevic and other
Yugoslav and Serbian leaders they will be held accountable for war
crimes. By Marlise Simons.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CLINTON (Washington) _ The president's activity today and
the choices facing the White House. By John M. Broder.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-AID (Washington) _ Developments on NATO efforts to help
the refugees. By Elizabeth Becker.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-VUKOVAR (Vukovar, Croatia) _ This ruined city beside the
Danube River is as good a place as any to meditate on the years of
misery and score-settling that lie ahead when the Serb campaign in
Kosovo comes to an end. By Blaine Harden.
</P>
<P>
   We are also considering, among others, stories on applying the
lessons of Bosnia to Kosovo, the basis in international law for the
NATO attacks, the vulnerabilities of stealthy aircraft and the
attack's impact on Irish neutrality.
</P>
