<P>
   ECON-REPORT (Undated) _ The government's final look at economic
growth in the fourth quarter shows that gross domestic product
expended at an annual rate of 6 percent, little changed from the
previous estimate of 6 percent. But after-tax corporate profits in
the quarter, reported for the first time today, fell 1 percent from
the third quarter and 3 percent from a year earlier. For all of
last year, corporate profits declined 2.2 percent, the first
decrease since a 4.8 percent drop in 1989. A second report shows
that orders to factories fell 2.5 percent in February. By Sylvia
Nasar.
