Organization, still divided about who should next head the body,
have failed to meet today's deadline for making a decision. The
United States is lobbying for Mike Moore, a former prime minister
of New Zealand. Other nations support Supachai Panitchpakdi, the
deputy prime minister of Thailand. The European Union has not
endorsed either candidate, although most of its members apparently
favor the Thai official. Leon Brittan, the European Union's trade
commissioner, complained today about some of the lobbying tactics
being used. By Elizabeth Olson.
