   POTTER-BESTSELLER (Undated) _ For a junior wizard, 11-year-old
Harry Potter has stirred up a steaming cauldron of Hogwart magic.
It has brought him fame, glory and an international copyright tiff.
The fictional Potter has soared into the popular imagination like a
loopy ride on his Nimbus 2000 broom. Last week, the first volume of
his adventures, ``Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone,'' outsold
more sober adult titles by the likes of Tom Wolfe, propelling this
British book to a pinnacle of best-sellerdom in the United States
never before achieved by a children's novel. By Doreen Carvajal.
</P>
