a decade ago, the do-it-yourself movement, both as an approach to
home decoration and as an outlook on life, has gone into decline,
giving way to the wide-ranging ``hire-it-out'' trend. Its credo is
simple: to save time, just delegate others to pick up the dry
cleaning, pamper the pets, coddle the offspring. By Jenny Lynn
Bader.
