<P>
   MAYA-LIN (Clinton, Tenn.) _ For eighteen years Maya Lin's
reputation has been etched in stone. ``Every time there was a
bombing or a plane crash, I would get a fax,'' the designer of the
Vietnam Veterans Memorial said. Eventually, Ms. Lin made a
conscious decision to avoid being typecast ``as a person whose work
concerns death and destruction.'' But proving that her
architectural reach extends beyond black granite monuments has
taken time. ``I need a body of work to come out for people to
realize how serious I am about this discipline,'' Ms. Lin, 39,
said. By Fred Bernstein.
