<P>
   F O O D A N D D I N I N G &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BUNDY-RECIPES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ A blast from the past: Recipes for hamburger toppings
and a French apple pie served at two old Fort Worth hamburger
emporiums. By BEVERLY BUNDY. Story will move in ``d'' food and
dining category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Hard-core baseball boycotters say I'm a wimp.
Nonboycotters say I'm ambivalent, indecisive, confused. People who
don't care about baseball one way or the other say it's fine by
them if I boycott _ or if I don't. They just want me to shut up
about it. I wish I could. But I can't. I've been boycotting, or
semi-boycotting, baseball for so long that I just can't stop _ and
I can't stop talking about it, either. By BILL THOMPSON. Story will
move in ``k'' commentary category &QL; 
