<HEADLINE>
JUST TRY TO GUESS WHAT ROCK &AMP; RYE IS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: When my sister and I were growing up in Detroit, we always
ordered Faygo Rock &AMP; Rye. Is that soft drink still available?
</P>
<P>
   _ G.W., Redwood City, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   A: Rock &AMP; Rye and other Faygo flavors can be ordered by calling
the Faygo Pop Shop at (248) 865-4767 or by visiting the World Wide
Web site www.faygo.com. Eight 2-liter bottles sell for $10.99, and
24 12-ounce cans for $8.99.
</P>
<P>
   Faygo was started in 1907 as Feigenson Brothers Bottling Works.
Founders Ben and Perry Feigenson used icing and baking recipes to
create the first three flavors: fruit punch, strawberry and grape.
They added Rock &AMP; Rye in 1922.
</P>
<P>
   In the 1930s the company adopted the Faygo name and moved to
Detroit, where it still operates. Redpop is Faygo's No. 1 flavor,
and Rock &AMP; Rye is still in the top five, according to a company
representative.
</P>
<P>
   Q: When was the last time the Sacramento Kings finished a season
with a winning record?
</P>
<P>
   _ T.S., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The last winning record was a 45-37 finish in the 1982-83
season, when the franchise was the Kansas City Kings.
</P>
<P>
   Larry Drew and Eddie Johnson were the star players on the team,
which did not make the playoffs. Teams with losing records reached
the first round of the National Basketball Association postseason
in 1985-86 and 1995-96.
</P>
<P>
   Six weeks after the last winning season, the Kings were sold for
$10.5 million to a Sacramento group. After suffering several years
of declining attendance in Kansas City, the franchise moved to
California in 1985.
</P>
<P>
   The Kings, who set an NBA record with their 15th consecutive
losing season last year, sold out every game in Sacramento from
1985 to 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Have Blythe Danner and her daughter Gwyneth Paltrow ever
worked together on a film?
</P>
<P>
   _ R.D., Whitehall, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   A: The Internet Movie Database turns up one project: the 1992 TV
miniseries ``Cruel Doubt.''
</P>
<P>
   Danner and Paltrow portray mother and daughter in the two-part
movie, which was Paltrow's third film appearance.
</P>
<P>
   They also provided voices for the 1997 Ken Burns documentary
``Thomas Jefferson'' and starred together in several plays at the
Williamstown Theatre.
</P>
<P>
   The Internet Movie Database is published at www.imdb.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
