<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   This multiple-choice exercise focuses on living American
authors. You pass with seven correct answers (a simple majority)
and earn an A with 10 right. Answers are on the opposite page.
</P>
<P>
   1. Ray Bradbury is author of (a) ``2001: A Space Odyssey;'' (b)
``Flowers for Algernon;'' (c) ``Dandelion Wine;'' (d) ``Dune''
</P>
<P>
   2. Joan Didion is author of (a) ``The White Hotel;'' (b) ``The
White Album;'' (c) ``The White Tower;'' (d) ``The White Company''
</P>
<P>
   3. The author of ``The Bluest Eye'' is (a) Gayl Jones; (b) James
Baldwin; (c) Richard Wright; (d) Toni Morrison
</P>
<P>
   4. The author of ``Horseman, Pass By'' is (a) Larry McMurtry;
(b) Rick Bass; (c) Richard Ford; (d) Winston Groom
</P>
<P>
   5. Ivan Doig is author of (a) ``This House of Sky;'' (b) ``Red
Sky at Morning; (c) ``The Big Sky;'' (d) ``The Crowded Sky''
</P>
<P>
   6. Alice McDermott is author of (a) ``Laughing Larry;'' (b)
``Good Time Charley;'' (c) ``Gus the Great;'' (d) ``Charming
Billy''
</P>
<P>
   7. The author of ``Them'' is (a) Diane Johnson; (b) Joyce Carol
Oates; (c) Thomas Berger; (d) Scott Spencer
</P>
<P>
   8. The author of ``A Flag for Sunrise'' is (a) Robert Stone; (b)
Paul Auster; (c) Mark Helprin; (d) E.L. Doctorow
</P>
<P>
   9. Gail Godwin is author of (a) ``Glass People;'' (b) ``The
Witches of Eastwick;'' (c) ``Palomino;'' (d) ``The Dean's
December''
</P>
<P>
   10. Tom Wolfe is author of (a) ``From Bauhaus to Our House;''
(b) ``Things That Go Bump in the Night;'' (c) ``Raise High the
Roofbeams, Carpenters;'' (d) ``Dinner at the Homesick Restaurant''
</P>
<P>
   11. The author of ``Cold Mountain'' is (a) Charles Frazier; (b)
Gloria Naylor; (c) Hortense Calisher; (d) Robert Roper
</P>
<P>
   12. The author of ``Pigs in Heaven'' is (a) Judy Blume; (b)
Carolyn Chute; (c) Barbara Kingsolver; (d) Fannie Flagg
Quiz answers: 1-c; 2-b; 3-a; 4-a; 5-a; 6-d; 7-b; 8-a; 9-a; 10-a;
11-a; 12-c
</P>
