(Sheeley/Hiskey/Rosen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BELLITEMS _ ATLANTA _ BellSouth odds/ends package. (Sheeley,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BELL-NORMAN _ ATLANTA _ A ``sick'' Greg Norman pulls out of
the BellSouth Classic, being held at the course he designed, TPC
Sugarloaf in Duluth. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   GLF-SUGARLOAF-FINISH _ When they made No. 18 at Sugarloaf,
officials hoped to build a strong par-5 finishing hole, similar to
the one at Atlanta Country Club, where tournaments often were won
and lost with risk-taking drives and approach shots. But No. 18 at
Sugarloaf hasn't provided the drama. In fact, as finishing holes
go, it needs a major overhaul. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   MASTERS-SHOPPING _ AUGUSTA, Ga. _ Augusta, Ga., is known for
it's famous country club and golf tournament, the Masters. However,
there's also plenty to do there besides watch a little dimpled
white ball soard through the air _ like, shop. The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution has produced a full page layout for use during
the week of the Masters (April 5-11) that includes text, photos,
and tips boxes on getting there and where to eat and stay.
(MJohnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
