   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-GATECH-EXPECTATIONS _ After a 10-2 record and a Gator Bowl
victory last season, expectations are high at Georgia Tech on the
eve of spring football practice. One of the biggest questions
heading into Friday's opening practice focuses on the defense,
which will have its third coordinator in as many years as former
Tech standout Ted Roof replaces Randy Edsall. The Jackets return
nine starters on offense, including All-America candidate Joe
Hamilton. (Clemons, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
