<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, April 1. If you
have
<TEXT>
<P>
   any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) - Since Friday, when Officer Marc Atkinson
was gunned down in an ambush in an industrial park west of the
freeway, all of the headlines and all of the TV newscasters and all
of the people who've stopped by at the improvised memorial at 30th
Avenue and Catalina have referred to him exactly that way _ as
``Officer`` Marc Atkinson. All the attention has been a comfort to
Atkinson's family, but they don't see him like we do. We mourn the
loss of a good cop. They mourn the loss of a good husband, a good
father, a good son, a good brother. By E.J. MONTINI. Story will
move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
