<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:COVER:APRIL-FOOLS-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COVER: CLASSIC PRANKS FOR APRIL FOOLS' DAY 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Includes one color slide of  
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   'Tis the day before April Fools',
</P>
<P>
   So make the most of this chance
</P>
<P>
   To trick friends and relatives with some fun-loving pranks.
</P>
<P>
   The sneaky CLASS ACTS team
</P>
<P>
   Has some crafty ideas up their sleeves
</P>
<P>
   That make getting a smile easy to achieve.
</P>
<P>
   Resist the urge to laugh when playing the jokes
</P>
<P>
   Or else you could be the one
</P>
<P>
   Who gets fooled next with a hoax!
</P>
<P>
   DOZENS OF WAYS TO TRICK YOUR FRIENDS AND FAMILY
</P>
<P>
   Set all the clocks three hours early.
</P>
<P>
   Put grape-flavored Kool-Aid in big sister's shower head.
</P>
<P>
   The dead fish in the bathtub or backpack is always a winner.
</P>
<P>
   Have big bro or sis move Mom or Dad's car to an unannounced
location.
</P>
<P>
   Put clear plastic wrap over the toilet seat, then grease the
doorknob so that a furious family member will become further
outraged. (Get ready for some serious heinie-whipping).
</P>
<P>
   Slip a plastic fly or other insect into a friend's drink or
sandwich at lunch.
</P>
<P>
   Drive your mom absolutely crazy by hiding her keys in her coat
pocket.
</P>
<P>
   Coat the driver's-side car-door handle with Vaseline.
</P>
<P>
   If you're a twin or have a sibling who looks like you, dress
alike for the day and try to pull a switcharoo on everyone.
</P>
<P>
   Tell a friend that his fly is open or that there's a rip in the
back of his jeans.
</P>
<P>
   Pretend you're giving a gift to a relative or friend. Get lots
of different-sized boxes and wrap them one by one with newspaper,
with each one inside the next larger one. In the smallest box, put
a note that says, ``April Fools'!''
</P>
<P>
   Conduct a panty raid and swap everyone's underwear.
</P>
<P>
   Hide a note from a ``long-lost secret admirer'' in a friend's
locker. Decorate the outside with dead flowers and black streamers.
</P>
<P>
   Fill the glove compartment with Silly String or marbles.
</P>
<P>
   Stick a fake dirty diaper into your friend's locker or book bag.
Buy a pre-made one or create one yourself by mixing peanut butter
with green food coloring.
</P>
<P>
   Secretly rearrange the shoes in Mom's closet or socks in Dad's
dresser drawer, mixing up the pairs so nothing matches.
</P>
<P>
   Mix up oatmeal and scoop a pile of it on the kitchen floor so it
looks like the cat threw up.
</P>
<P>
   Or mix up oatmeal and pretend you're throwing up so you don't
have to go to school. Trick Mom later with ``April Fools'.''
</P>
<P>
   Shake up a person's soft drink so it will fizz in her face.
</P>
<P>
   Tie a $5 bill onto fishing line and strategically place it in
the hallway at school. Yank on the string as the person reaches for
it.
</P>
<P>
   Put salt in the sugar bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Reach out to shake a friend's hand in the morning, holding a
handful of shaving cream.
</P>
<P>
   Wake up early and stash the morning paper in the refrigerator.
</P>
<P>
   Put fake or candy worms in your brother's shoes.
</P>
<P>
   Hide the charger or power cord of Mom's cellular phone.
</P>
<P>
   Remove the batteries of Dad's pager.
</P>
<P>
   Fix French toast. Substitute baking soda for powered sugar.
</P>
<P>
   Wake up Dad or big brother super early to say the car has two
flat tires.
</P>
<P>
   Chew up black licorice and spit it out, gagging all your
friends.
</P>
<P>
   Early in the morning, put a few cubes of ice on Mom's pillow or
in her slippers.
</P>
