<HEADLINE>
TRENDS: HIP STUFF FROM THE PLANET SHOP-A-LOT 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Includes one color slide of Kendra Newton modeling capri pants.
(Credit: Photo by Hillery Smith Garrison. Courtesy of the Fort
Worth Star-Telegram.) 
 By KELLY DEGARMO 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Capri Craze
</P>
<P>
   Those short pants ruling the racks in stores are the hottest
look for spring. Known as capri pants, clam diggers, pedal pushers
or cropped pants, they are a great warm-weather alternative to
shorts. Passing the school dress code should be no prob. Capris
look great with just about any style top _ oversize or skimpy.
</P>
<P>
   Backpack Books
</P>
<P>
   Build your own portable library with American Girl's new
collectible Backpack Books ($1.95 each). The miniature books
contain colorful metal key chains that can be attached to a
backpack, travel bag or other Backpack Books. Titles include ``50
Best Babysitting Tips,'' ``Learn a Little Sign Language,'' ``Miles
of Smiles!'' ``Backseat Games,'' ``Homesick Blues?'' and others.
</P>
<P>
   For a free American Girl catalog, call (800) 845-0005 or check
out the Web site at www.americangirl.com.
</P>
<P>
   Palm-Size e-mail
</P>
<P>
   Electronic mail is definitely the hip way to communicate. One of
the latest new gadgets is the e-message center called
``friend.link'' from Playmates Toys ($20). For age 8 and up, the
hand-held unit can broadcast a message, send a private note, detect
a nearby friend or tell a fortune. Available in flashy colors,
friend.link comes with a key chain to attach to belts and
backpacks. Two or more units are required to link up with a friend
and communicate. Each unit requires three AAA batteries.
</P>
<P>
   Mail-Order Goes Young
</P>
<P>
   Good news for young and/or petite girls who like the popular
Delia's catalog. There's a new version _ Delia's dot dot dash _ for
girls sizes 4 to 16. Just like its big sister Delia, the dot dot
dash catalog offers way-cool clothes, such as pedal pushers, tank
tops, flare jeans, board shorts, platform sandals, butterfly hair
clips and other stuff. If buying isn't an option, scope out the
colorful pages for style ideas. For a free copy of Delia's dot dot
dash, call (877) DOT DASH ( 877) 368-3274 or go online at
www.dotdotdash.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
