<HEADLINE>
NEW VIDEO RELEASES 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By ANGELICA LARA 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The Wonderful Ice Cream Suit''
</P>
<P>
   Starring: Edward James Olmos, Esai Morales, and Joe Mantegna.
</P>
<P>
   Plot: Five down-on-their-luck Los Angeles guys hope to change
their lives by pooling their money to buy a magical white suit. The
men arrange to wear the suit for one night each (but decide to wear
it for one hour each in one evening), and the outfit helps make
each of their dreams come true.
</P>
<P>
   Why go see it?: This film, released only on video, is a
heartwarming tale of friendship, hope and sharing. It mixes comedy
with serious thought and makes you think while you laugh. If you
love movies about giving, friendship and magic, along with
slapstick comedy, then check out ``The Wonderful Ice Cream Suit.''
The screenplay was written by Ray Bradbury.
</P>
<P>
   Reason for rating: It was rated PG, but I couldn't figure out
why. There was no inappropriate language or subject matter, and the
violence was only a little slapstick fighting. The only thing that
might be a cause for the rating was one scene in a bar.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 rating: 9.
</P>
<P>
   Also available:
</P>
<P>
   ``Mighty Joe Young''
</P>
<P>
   Starring Bill Paxton and Charlize Theron.
</P>
<P>
   A live-action film about a 15-foot-tall gorilla whose life is
threatened by poachers. A zoologist and a woman who raised the
gorilla work together to rescue him and bring him to a California
animal preserve.
</P>
<P>
   Available now. Cost $24.99.
</P>
<P>
   Rated PG.
</P>
