<HEADLINE>
STAR STRUCK? CHECK OUT YOUR WEEK 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By Students SARABETH BALON and NICK FOREMAN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before finalizing your activities, take time to read the
following horoscope, which is a fun way to plan your week.
</P>
<P>
   ARIES (March 21 - April 19): Procrastination is a horrible
thing. Although initially it seems wonderful, you always regret it
in the end. When you are given a project, begin to work on it
immediately. If you choose to delay, you will become very
frustrated and stressed. Get to work!
</P>
<P>
   TAURUS (April 20 - May 20): The time has come for you to take up
a new hobby. Do something that you have wanted to do for a very
long time. If you find yourself a little wary of the experience, do
a bit of research. Finding out the facts will calm your nerves, and
you will be set to take the plunge into this new activity.
</P>
<P>
   GEMINI (May 21 - June 20): You will receive a money bonus in the
next few days. Be a wise spender, but the key word is ``spend.''
Every once in a while, you need to splurge and treat yourself to
something special. It is a chance for you to bask in the pleasures
produced by your hard work. Happy shopping!
</P>
<P>
   CANCER (June 21 - July 22): This week, you will find yourself
the bearer of bad news. Sometimes when you have something that is
difficult to say, it is easier to say it quickly. If you choose to
sugarcoat it, the message may become too vague and/or the person
you are talking to might be insulted by your indirectness.
</P>
<P>
   LEO (July 23 - Aug. 22): Things are running smoothly in your
life. Your circle of friends is getting along better than ever.
Your family life is going great. Enjoy the serenity that surrounds
you this week. Keep in mind that some people work their whole lives
for what you have.
</P>
<P>
   VIRGO (Aug. 23 - Sept. 22): You need to do a little
soul-searching. Lately you have been down in the dumps and only you
know why. Figure it out. It is affecting everyone you encounter.
Your friends and family love you and would help, except you've put
up a barrier that is difficult to break through. Let someone in.
</P>
<P>
   LIBRA (Sept. 23 - Oct. 22): Too many things are going too well
for you and they will continue to roll that way this week. Don't
get spoiled by all the attention. Learn to let others share the
spotlight. Things will begin to slow down next week.
</P>
<P>
   SCORPIO (Oct. 23 - Nov. 21): This week holds a rough start but a
smooth finish. By Wednesday, you might need to take a break and
relieve some stress. After that's out of the way, the week will be
great. Some people say that time flies when you are having fun, but
this week, time will slow down and let you enjoy yourself.
</P>
<P>
   SAGITTARIUS (Nov. 22 - Dec. 21): You may feel a little neglected
this week. However, it is probably just in your head and you are it
out of proportion. You are still loved by all and you still have
your cutie. Keep from getting into deep thoughts about this because
you will end up driving yourself up the wall. When you catch
yourself daydreaming, open a book or turn on the radio.
</P>
<P>
   CAPRICORN (Dec. 22 - Jan. 19): The more that you think that
things are way too hectic and busy, the less you get finished. Do
not waste your precious time worrying. That never does anyone any
good. Get home from school and start your work right off the bat.
That way, you might get a little relaxation before you conk out.
</P>
<P>
   AQUARIUS (Jan. 20 - Feb. 18): There is a lot of truth in the
phrase, ``There is no I in Team.'' It may be hard for you to allow
someone else do the job without your help, but they will never
learn if you do not stop trying to be the universal player. Teams
grow together and that is hard to do when somebody is stealing the
spotlight. Use what you have to teach others.
</P>
<P>
   PISCES (Feb. 19 - March 20): This week, you will have time to
yourself. It is up to you how you spend it. You could twiddle your
thumbs, or you could use it to find what you have been looking for
in the past couple of weeks. Sit and think, then get something
accomplished. This time will not come around too often, so take
advantage of it.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
