</P>
<P>
   Y2K-REPORT (Washington) _ The White House says that 92 percent
of the federal government's essential computer systems are ready
for the year 2000, but predicts that Americans will have difficulty
reaching some foreign countries by telephone or airplane next year,
because their computers will not be fixed in time. By Robert Pear.
(Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
