will outline his vision of how his country's creations in those
fields will move it toward a freer, more market-based economy.
</P>
<P>
   The prime minister's speech in Kresge Auditorium will be
broadcast around the world by CNN and in China by official
television.
</P>
<P>
   ``As Americans, we tend to think everything of importance tends
to be invented in the United States, and China looks like just a
big market to us,'' said Suzanne Berger, head of the MIT
International Science and Technology Initiative. ``We don't
understand that knowledge today is being created in many different
centers in the world, and China will be a major center. The Chinese
will be our colleagues, and they will also be a center of knowledge
creation. We're going to see big things coming out of China.''
</P>
<P>
   The announcement of Zhu's US visit in mid-March came amid
tensions over a Chinese spy who the US government said stole
