<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-KOSOVO-MISSING-NYT, which moved
in ``i'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``They came under small-arms fire. They reported over the radio
that they were surrounded. No more was heard from them.''
</P>
<P>
   _KENNETH BACON, the Pentagon spokesman, reporting that three
American soldiers are missing.
</P>
