WIND-ARIZ _ It tipped over trucks, caused one death in a
multiple-car pileup and blew off roofs in northern Arizona. It
kicked up dust so thick in the Valley that it looked like snow.
Wednesday's gale was one of the worst northern Arizona has ever
experienced, with gusts as high as 104 mph. Much of central and
eastern Arizona were under high-wind warnings all day Wednesday,
and parts of Interstate 40 remained closed early today. By MAUREEN
WEST. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL;
